 throw an `Error`, so that's good to note.\\n\\nThen, there's the empty `QdoxTest` public class. I’m wondering if an empty class is acceptable. Maybe checkstyle has rules about needing at least one test. Since it doesn’t really serve a purpose, I think we should delete it.\\n\\nThough, since there’s no delete tool, I could use bash for this operation. Removing it would reduce noise, and it also isn’t mapped to any useful tests. I believe deleting `QdoxTest.java` is the best choice since it's an unnecessary placeholder.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Deciding on test file management**\\n\\nI’m reviewing the existing tests, and it looks like there's just a placeholder. I need to add a dedicated file since the empty `QdoxTest` class is an extra top-level class and doesn’t map to dynamic access.\\n\\nAccording to the rules, there should be a one-to-one mapping between the dynamic-access report classes and the generated test files. Keeping the placeholder might violate this, especially since the generated suite should only include `JavaDocBuilderTest`.\\n\\nSo, I think it’s best to delete the placeholder. I’ll use bash to run the `rm` command for this.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_09Rz7sVNfL6VtrrEdKmNZfAm|fc_0da86e1da14251580169f6179e3a1081a1adc6ab1dd7ce5aa5", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rm tests/src/com.thoughtworks.qdox/qdox/1.12.1/src/test/java/com_thoughtworks_qdox/qdox/QdoxTest.java", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 817, "output": 564, "cacheRead": 26624, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28005, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777735569969, "responseId": "resp_0da86e1da14251580169f6179270d881a1a5c5aa21dd78a0ac"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_09Rz7sVNfL6VtrrEdKmNZfAm|fc_0da86e1da14251580169f6179e3a1081a1adc6ab1dd7ce5aa5", "toolName": "bash", "con